Read: task-IL removes cross-task head competition, so baselines are near-ceiling (naive 0.93-0.98, er 0.97-0.99) and gain adds ~0 on top / hurts under SGD. The one clean effect is SGD naive+gain forgetting = 0.0000 (frozen subnet, no momentum, no replay). Residual forgetting elsewhere is Adam momentum nudging frozen params + ER retuning within-task head biases — NOT the class-IL cross-task bias leak (that is gone). Same oracle caveat.
